column88: One way to prepare for a visit to a clinic or health care center is to: 1) Be you, be honest; 2) Use "I" statements; and 3) Ask your questions.Imagine a young man who is having sex with other men. He goes to his local clinic because he has been experiencing burning when he pees. His provider changes the conversation topic to medications that can reduce the risk of getting HIV/AIDS. The young man clarifies that he wants to get tested for other STIs first. After getting tested, he asks his provider about how those medications work, as well as when he should expect his test results.Which of the following best illustrates how this young man used "Step 1: Be you, be honest"?
